name: national-agricultural-imagery-program-naip-digital-georectified-images-minnesota-2004-interim-p
notes: This INTERIM data set contains photographic information obtained for the National Agricultural Imagery Program (NAIP) and is comprised of scanned photographs that were acquired on color positive film. Acquisition was leaf-on with mature crops prior to harvest. Images are 2-meter resolution and have been georectified (see Lineage and Horizontal Positional Accuracy for information on how georectification differs from orthorectification). NAIP imagery is quarter-quadrangle centered to provide consistent and repeatable coverage. The quarter-quad photos have been mosaicked into MrSID format county files. The interim product has been created to provide timely information for the Farm Service Agency's compliance program. FSA is distributing the interim product ONLY with the understanding that the images have not yet undergone FSA's comprehensive quality assurance inspection process that may require corrections and possible replacement of the imagery. (Note that FSA provides one metadata record per MrSID county file; the Land Management Information Center created this metadata record to describe the whole data set. For more information, also see FSA's NAIP website: http://www.apfo.usda.gov/naip.html )
